==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: gall-of-the-earth
<hw>gall-of-the-earth</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A common perennial herb
(<spn>Nabalus serpentarius</spn>) widely distributed in southern and
eastern U. S., having drooping clusters of pinkish flowers and thick
basal leaves suggesting a lion's foot in shape; sometimes placed in the
genus <gen>Prenanthes</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> lion's foot, gall of the earth, <spn>Nabalus
serpentarius</spn>, <spn>Prenanthes serpentaria</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gallomania</ent>⟦br⟧
